The measles, mumps, and rubella (MMR) vaccine is recommended for all children. It protects against 3 potentially serious illnesses. The vaccine is very effective at preventing disease. After 1 dose, 85 percent of children 9 months of age and 95 percent over 12 months of age are immune. Nearly all of those who do not develop immunity after the 1st dose develop it after a 2nd dose. - Mod.LK]
